		Version information about the chip and driver such as chip id, firmware
		version date and time codes in human readable format

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/status
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		Driver status and state information printed in human readable format

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/addr
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		i2c 16-bit register address input to send manual i2c commands

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/count
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		i2c count input to send manual i2c commands in number of bytes to read/write

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/data
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		i2c data information to send manual i2c commands in 0xAA 0xBB 0xCC format

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/ccreset
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		Reset the in-band communication channel between RX and TX

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/txbusy
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		Check if the in-band communication channel is busy transmitting

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/txdone
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		Check if the transmission over in-band communication channel is done

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/txlen
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		Number of bytes to transmit in the in-band communication channel

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/rxlen
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		Number of bytes received in the in-band communication channel

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/rxdone
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		Whether the in-band communication channel data receiving is complete

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/features
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		Supported feature mask in the format "id:features". id=0 corresponds to just set
		current session

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/authtype
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		Authentication type to run (0 = Bidi, others = WPC packet types)

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/wpc_ready
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		Check this node to see if the driver/HW is ready for WPC authentication

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/ap5v_gpio
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
Description:
		Read or set the AP5V GPIO value

What:		/sys/class/power_supply/wireless/device/mode_gpio_status
Contact:	pixel-bms-sw@google.com
